opening_comment: Hi, the boarder between Marocco und Western Sahara is not correct. You are showing the area of western sahara which is occupied by Marocco as maroccan territory, though it is still Western Sahara Territoy. Sources: - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Sahara - https://www.google.com/maps/place/Western+Sahara/@24.0570723,-15.7021883,7z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0xc22482523302153:0xb7a6f81873dfd75a!8m2!3d24.215527!4d-12.885834!16zL20vMDgycWs?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDUxNS4wIKXMDSoJLDEwMjExNDU1SAFQAw%3D%3D  Thank you, Ben
closing_comment: OSM notes is kinda wrong place for this type of discussion if regular mapper would try to change border without proper discussion their changes will just be reverted.  First of all there are bunch of different boundaries:   Western Sahara - https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/2559126 Morocco except Western Sahara - https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/13407035 Morocco - https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/3630439   To understand how disputed territories are mapped in OpenStreetMap read this: https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Disputed_territories  There is also few useful link in Western Sahara part of this page. More details  and how to find previous discussions on this topic:  https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Disputed_territories#Africa  If you still think it is mapped wrongly than you can try to comment in one of the previous discussions. But realistically it will take way more than just link to Wikipedia con convince people to change it.
